cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the detection of adversarial attacks on artificial neural networks, which is a common problem in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the behavior of neural networks and the importance of single input neurons, which could fall under the sub-categories cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
